Walt Disney Co. incorporated feng shui into Hong Kong Disneyland's design, consulting experts for guidance.
The park's layout, groundbreaking, and opening dates were all influenced by feng shui principles.
Despite hopes for economic growth, skeptics question the park's impact on the local economy.
Concerns about overcrowding and environmental impact have also been raised.
To address these issues, the park plans a phased opening and has made preparations for a smooth start.
Ticket sales have been successful, with all opening day tickets sold out.
Hong Kong Disneyland aims to attract visitors from mainland China and transform into a family-friendly tourist destination.
